JobAttrAlwaysReplenishFullDependencesDes: If true, MRP does not consider the quantity produced from the WO when generating dependencies. Consider the full amount. Default: false
JobAttrConsiderDependencesOnFinishedOper: If true, load all the allocations of the Work Order, including allocations vinculated to closed operations. Default: false
JobAttrConsiderReleasedAndProductionPOsA: If true, if the WO has a status [In Production] or [Released], it considers the WO date as being for the first day of MRP, so that the components are not allocated to other OPs with a previous date that do not have these statuses. If false, OPs with a status of [In Production] or [Released] have no priority over others and the work date for each will be considered. Default: true
JobAttrConsiderReserveDesc: if true, MRP considers Locked = 1 allocations as already used and does not recalculate them. If false, MRP does not consider Locked = 1 allocations as already used and recalculates them. Default: true
JobAttrDayToStartPlanningPeriodDesc: If filled, the master plan will consider the filled day as the day that planning always begins. Fill in from 1 to 28. If not filled, the current day will be considered as the beginning.
JobAttrEndTimeDesc: If this parameter is filled in, the end date of the schedule will be replaced by the date filled in here. Default: StartTime + Horizonte
JobAttrGroupTypeDesc: If filled with "BYORDER", MRP will supply each requirement individually instead of grouping by day. Default: (ByDay)
JobAttrHorizonDesc: Defines the MRP calculation horizon in days. Default: 720 days
JobAttrHorizonteDesc: Number of days to be scheduled from the start date of the schedule. Default: 90
JobAttrIgnoreDependencesDesc: When checking if stock is ok, allow the scheduler to ignore RawMaterial or Component dependence. That will make the WO be scheduled even if there is no stock available for it.
JobAttrIgnoreMaxPlannedOrderReplenishCon: True, causes MRP to ignore the limitation of creating more than 10 WOs for replenishment
JobAttrIgnorePastDemandsDesc: Defines whether to ignore demands prior to the planning start date. Usually used in conjunction with DayToStartPlanningPeriod. Default: FALSE
JobAttrIgnoreStockAllocationsWhenCheckin: Ignore inventory allocation when checking components. Default: false
JobAttrIsAllowedToAddStockAllocationsDes: If true, MRP can add new inventory allocations. If false, MRP will not create new allocations. Default: TRUE
JobAttrIsAllowedToRemoveStockAllocations: If true, MRP can delete inventory allocations. If false, MRP will not remove existing allocations. Default: TRUE
JobAttrMaskFormatMPS: Defines the prefix that MPS will use to create new WOs. Default: "MPS-"
JobAttrMaskFormatMRP: Defines the prefix that MRP will use to create new WOs. Default: "MRP-"
JobAttrMasterCalendarDesc: Calendar ID to be used by MRP to know which days the resources work and which days do not work
JobAttrMustAllocateFullQuantityWhenThere: Must allocate complete batch of the dependent when there is surplus in the allocation. (default: false)
JobAttrMustReplenishMinStockDesc: Defines whether MPS is responsible for replenishing material until MinStock is reached. Usually used when this control is not done through Forecasts. Default: TRUE
JobAttrMustReplenishMinStockForFinshedMa: Must replenish min stock for Finished Materials. (default: true)
JobAttrMustSplitReplenishPlannedOrderByL: If true, causes the MRP to divide the replacement OPs by the quantity filled in the "Replacement Lot " field of the material
JobAttrNumberOfDaysToAddToPOSupplyingSto: If filled, it indicates a number of days to add to the EDD of the WOs that are only serving inventory. To leave the WOs that are serving orders as a priority. Default: 0
JobAttrPIDDesc: Project ID, listed on Gantt, to run the job
JobAttrPurchaseRequestsGroupTypeDesc: If filled with "BYORDER", MRP will supply purchase requests individually instead of grouping by day. Default: (ByDay)
JobAttrReallocateDesc: If filled with "ALL", MRP removes all allocations before starting the calculation. Default: (empty)
JobAttrResourcesToSaveUsageAndCapacityDe: Types of resources to consider when saving capacity and occupation. Default: Primary.
JobAttrRunAllocationBeforeMRPDesc: Defines whether to run the allocation routine before running MRP. Default: FALSE
JobAttrSaveAllocationsDesc: Save ALOCATIONS, overriding MRP. Default: FALSE
JobAttrSaveOperationSchedulesDesc: Saves quantities schedules by period/day on table PlannedOrderOperationSchedules. Default: false
JobAttrSavePlannedOrderRelationsDesc: Saves lists of production orders. Default: true
JobAttrSaveResourceShiftSchedulesDesc: Saves resource's availabilities by period/day on table ResourceShiftSchedules. Default: false
JobAttrSaveResourceUsageByDateDesc: Saves resource's availabilities and usage by day on table ResourceUsageByDates. Default: false
JobAttrStartTimeDesc: If this parameter is filled in, the schedule start date will be replaced by the date filled in here. Default: Date / Time the user clicked the Optimize button
